  "commentary": "ABOUT [ edit ]\n\nBank of Baroda is engaged in providing various services, such as personal banking, corporate banking, international banking, small and medium enterprise (SME) banking, rural banking, non-resident Indian (NRI) services and treasury services.(Source : Company Web-site)\n\nKEY POINTS [ edit ]\n\nMarket Position\nThe bank is among India\u2019s top five banks by asset size and total deposits with a 6% market share as of FY24. [1]\n\nRevenue Mix\nRetail Banking: 39% in Q3 FY26 vs 35% in FY22\nWholesale Banking: 32% in Q3 FY26 vs 31% in FY22\nTreasury: 21% in Q3 FY26 vs 29% in FY22\nOthers: 8% in Q3 FY26 vs 5% in FY22 [2][3]\n\nKey Ratios\nCRAR: 16.47% in Q3 FY26 vs 16.31% in FY22[4]\nGNPA: 2.04% in Q3 FY26 vs 6.61% in FY22\nNNPA: 0.57% in Q3 FY26 vs 1.72% in FY22\nPCR: 92.73% in Q3 FY26 vs 88.71% in FY22 [5]\nYield on Advances: 7.56% in Q3 FY26 vs 6.79% in FY22\nCost of Deposits: 4.75% in Q3 FY26 vs 3.52% in FY22\nNIM: 2.79% in Q3 FY26 vs 3.03% in FY22 [6][7]\n\nBranch Network[8]\nAs of Q3FY 26, the bank operates in 8,500 branches, 11,563 ATMs, 7,546 Self service passbooks, 2,034 Cash Recyclers. Overall digital touch points were 19,185 with 1148 Cr transactions.\n\nBranch Break-Up FY25:[9]\nRural: 35%\nSemi-Urban: 26%\nMetro: 21.5%\nUrban: 18%\n\nAdvances[10]\nThe gross domestic advances of the bank were Rs. 13,44,904 Cr as of Q3 FY26 vs Rs. 11,73,034 Cr as of Q3 FY25.\n\nAdvance Mix:[10]\nCorporate: 38%\nRetail: 31%\nAgriculture: 16%\nMSME: 15%\n\nDeposits[11]\nAs of Q3 FY26, the bank has total domestic deposits of Rs. 15,46,749 Cr compared to Rs. 14,02,909 Cr in Q3 FY25.\n\nDeposits Mix:[11]\nTerm Deposits: 62%\nSavings Deposits: 32%\nCurrent Deposits: 6%\n\nInternational Business[8]\nThe Bank has 80 overseas offices across 15 countries including 37 overseas branches, 1 IBU in GIFT City, Gujarat, and 9 EBSUs in UAE, 52 branches of the Bank\u2019s 7 overseas subsidiaries. In addition, It has one Joint Venture, India International Bank in Malaysia, and one associate bank, Indo Zambia Bank Ltd. in Zambia with 32 branches. The international business accounts for 18% of the gross advances and 15% of the total deposits as of Q3 FY26. [12][10][11]\n\nDigital Initiatives\nThe bank offers digital banking solutions like BoB World, BoB World UPI, Baroda Connect, Debit Cards, Prepaid Cards, BHIM Aadhaar, ATM and Cash Recycler machines, Self Service Passbook Printers, TAB Banking, etc. As of Q3 FY26, 96% of the bank's transactions are done digitally. It is ranked 2nd in terms of debit card issuance and 3rd in terms of UPI remittance. [13][14]\n\nRegulatory Ban\nIn October 2023, the RBI instructed the bank to halt onboarding new customers via its mobile application, BoB World, citing material supervisory concerns related to internal audit lapses. In May 2024, the RBI lifted these restrictions. [15] [16]\n\nFocus[17]\nThe bank expects a deposit growth of 9% to 11% and a loan book growth of 11% to 13%. It aims for a margin of 2.85% to 3% for the gull year.\n\nSubsidiary[18]\nBank has received approval from the RBI to establish a wholly owned subsidiary for undertaking Standalone Primary Dealer (SPD) business by infusing capital of up to Rs.2000 crores subject to specified conditions.\n\nBond Issuance[19]\nBank\u2019s board approved raising long-term bonds up to \u20b910,000 crore, in addition to \u20b95,000 crore remaining from earlier approval, taking the total fundraising limit to \u20b915,000 crore via infrastructure and affordable housing/green infrastructure bonds in FY26 and beyond, issued in single or multiple tranches.\n\nManagement Changes[20][21]\nMrs Mini T ceased from the position of CGM - Zonal Head on account of identification as Executive Director in Indian Bank effective 24th Nov 2025. Mrs. Archana Pandey superannuated from the position of Head Internal Audit and replaced by Mrs. Kavita Singh.\n\nLast edited 2\u00a0months, 3\u00a0weeks ago\n Request an update \n\n\u00a9 Protected by Copyright",
